race.comment: LADY COCO (8) was back to her best, beaten 1.3L here second-up over a shorter sprint. Draws better today, and the step-up in trip suits. The in-form Galati stays aboard and on a quick backup, she rates to break through. VALID POINT (5) resumes for the Wolfe yard and owns a Lark Hill trial win over 950m. Faithfull rode in that and stays aboard today. Has a wide gate, but he can return much improved. EL FOXIE (3) resumed in the LADY COCO race for a new barn and came from last, beaten 3.4L. It wasn't a bad effort under the circumstances, and he will be fitter again. Well placed with the 3kg claim and can get into the money. NO COMEBACKS (6) didn't do a bad job here on debut, and the 2kg claimer will position forward again from the inside gate. Has upside and is in the mix.
